The Pap test in HIV-positive women. The aim of this work was to estimate the frequency of abnormal Papanicolau (Pap) smears in a group of HIV-infected women undergoing cervical screening. We re-examined 162 Pap smears from 118 patients infected with HIV. The patients were aged 23-55 years. A total of 108 smears (66.6%) from 80 patients were negative 14 smears (8.6%) from 14 patients showed inflammation